d’s music and public persona but the very heart of American culture.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aCountry musicxHistory and criticism. 0aCountry musicianszUnited StatesvBiography. 7aMUSIC / General.2bisacsh  aMerle Haggard, outlaw country, music criticism.  abiography, country music, country music performers, country music history.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Texas Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311076651640uhttps://doi.org/10.7560/32236-940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781477325681423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781477325681/original  a978-3-11-076651-6  University of Texas Press Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  aEBA_EMB  aGBV-deGruyter-alles